<section class="faq">
  <h2>FAQ: Updating Quotes</h2>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>How do I edit a quote?</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Go to your home page.</li>
      <li>find the quote you want to edit.</li>
      <li>Click the <strong>Edit</strong> button.</li>
      <li>Make your changes in the text field.</li>
      <li>Press <strong>Publish</strong> to confirm.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>Who can update a quote?</h3>
    <p>
      Only the user who originally posted the quote can update it. If you don’t see
      the <strong>Edit</strong> option, you may not have permission.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>Can I update a quote after posting it?</h3>
    <p>
      Yes! Quotes can be updated at any time after they are posted.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>What happens after I update a quote?</h3>
    <p>Once you save your changes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>The quote will immediately show the updated text.</li>
      <li>Previous versions are replaced by the new one.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>Can I undo an update?</h3>
    <p>
      Currently, updates cannot be undone. If you make a mistake, you can edit the
      quote again and fix it manually.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>Why can’t I edit my quote?</h3>
    <p>This may happen if:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>You’re not logged into the account that posted the quote.</li>
      <li>The quote has been deleted.</li>
      <li>There’s a temporary connection issue. Try refreshing the page.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>The update isn’t saving, what should I do?</h3>
    <p>Try the following:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Make sure the quote text isn’t empty.</li>
      <li>Check your internet connection.</li>
      <li>Refresh the app and try again.</li>
      <li>If the problem continues, contact support.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

